race.comment: CHEWING GUM (7) brings placing from Mornington and Sandown-Hillside and with the extra fitness is well placed to win. Ethan Brown sticks aboard from those and she should enjoy a cosy run. In a leading yard and should have them covered. BOLTSAVER (1) didn't get into it after a slow start at Benalla in a 70. Wasn't beaten far in a 78 at Randwick prior and missed twice by 1L at Sandown-Hillside before that. Well placed and John Allen may get the best out of him. GISELLA (10) is an improver who can build on the Maiden win this track. TIZ TIME (8) enjoys some give in the track and should get that today. She's a capable galloper who can't be ruled out.
